egoli.net|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref>{{Primary source inline|date=April 2020}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artribune.com/report/2016/04/mostra-esther-stocker-palazzo-metternich-vienna/|title=Geometrie d\u2019artista. Esther Stocker a Vienna - Artribune|first=Franco|last=Veremondi|date=11 April 2016|publisher=|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.parnass.at/aktuelles/esther-stocker-im-palais-metternich|title=Esther Stocker im Palais Metternich - PARNASS Kunstmagazin|first=|last=http://www.pion.at/|website=www.parnass.at|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://divisare.com/projects/317965-esther-stocker-geometrien|title=Esther Stocker \u00b7 Geometrien|website=Divisare|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref>\n* 2016, GPLcontemporary Vienna: exhibition ''<nowiki/>'Im Keller' im Keller'' by [[Ulrich Seidl]]; Intervention/action 'Scandalous pictures' by Pablo Chiereghin, artist, Andrea Hubin, research assistant at [[Kunsthalle Wien]], and Karin Schneider, art historian and art educator; Curated by Marcello Farabegoli.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marcello-farabegoli.net/ulrich-seidl.html|title=Ulrich Seidl|website=www.marcello-farabegoli.net|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref>{{Primary source inline|date=April 2020}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ulrichseidl.com/en/ulrich-seidl-director/other-works/exhibitions|title=Ulrich Seidl \u2013 Exhibitions|website=www.ulrichseidl.com|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>[http://wien.orf.at/news/stories/2763073/ Article by] [[ORF (broadcaster)|ORF]] (Austrian Broadcasting Corporation), March 17, 2016</ref>\n* 2015, special project of the Vienna Art Week at [[KunstHausWien]] / Museum Hundertwasser: exhibition ''Perpetuum Mobile''<nowiki/> with Flavia Bigi, Pablo Chiereghin, Fanni Futterknecht, Gianmaria Gava in collaboration with Anke Armandi & Agnes Peschta, Aiko Kazuko Kurosaki, Sissa Micheli, Linus Riepler, and [[Hana Usui]] curated by Marcello Farabegoli.<ref>{{cite 