ienna-show-1697463|title=The Japanese Embassy in Austria Has Withdrawn Support for a Show That Includes Controversial Japanese Artists. November 6, 2019|website=www.artnet.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://apps.derstandard.at/privacywall/story/2000110847491/kritische-kunst-ueber-japan-japanik-um-wiener-ausstellung|title=Kritische Kunst \u00fcber Japan: Japanik um Wiener Ausstellung. 9. November 2019|website=www.derstandard.at}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.artribune.com/dal-mondo/2019/11/mostra-japan-unlimited-vienna/|title=Japan Unlimited. Giappone vs Austria per \u201ccolpa\u201d di una mostra. 9 Novembre 2019|website=www.artribune.com}}</ref>\n* 2017, special project of the Vienna Art Week at ARCC.art open space: exhibition ''Carmine'' by Ben G. Fodor and round table about Art & Science with [[Georg Gottlob]], professor of informatics at Oxford University & TU-Vienna, Gerfried Stocker, artistic director of [[Ars Electronica]], Ben G. Fodor, artist, and Marcello Farabegoli, curator of the exhibition / moderated by Dorothee Frank, journalist at [[\u00d61]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://2017.viennaartweek.at/en/program/ausstellung-ben-g-fodor-carmine|title=Exhibition: Ben G. Fodor, \u00bbCarmine\u00ab|first=VIENNA ART WEEK|last=2017|website=VIENNA ART WEEK 2017|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marcello-farabegoli.net/carmine.html|title=Carmine|website=www.marcello-farabegoli.net|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref>{{Primary source inline|date=April 2020}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.artmagazine.cc/content100479.html|title=Ben G. Fodor - Carmine: Rote Liniengef\u00fcge auf Schwarz|website=www.artmagazine.cc|accessdate=24 February 2018}}</ref><ref>[https://www.salto.bz/de/article/29112017/kunst-auf-der-parabolischen-bahn Article by Martina Genetti in salto.bz (Italian-German newsportal for] [[South Tyrol|South Tirol]]), November 30, 2017</ref>\n* 2017, section project statements of the Parallel Vienna: ''Parallel & concordan